P03.Name: Ripple effect, 2022
P03.Tagline: Discover Ripple effect, a public artwork in Parramatta celebrating connection to Country, water, shared histories and community stories
P03.Description: Water is essential to life, and human history tells us that thriving civilisations are born around the riverbanks. The artist Syedâ€™s affinity for water resonates with the history of the first known residents along the Indus River in Sindh, Pakistan, specifically the Mohenjo-Daro (part of a larger culture known as the Harappans), as well as with the Parramatta River and its waterways, its Indigenous people, and the evolving culture.
